=== {{捷克}} ===
1991年，[[捷克斯洛伐克|捷克斯洛伐克]]对《刑法》进行修订，其中第260条提及纳粹主义和共产主义，禁止宣传限制人权和自由的运动。后来，由于缺乏明确的法律定义，对这些内容的具体提及被删除。尽管如此，法律本身还是符合宪法的。<ref name="khpg">{{Cite web|title=Analysis of the Law on Prohibiting Communist Symbols - Human Rights in Ukraine|url=http://khpg.org/en/index.php?id=1430564974|accessdate=2017-08-17|work=Kharkiv Human Rights Protection Group|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817162709/http://khpg.org/en/index.php?id=1430564974|archivedate=2017-08-17|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Joint amicus curiae brief for the Constitutional Court of Moldova on the compatibility with European standards|url=https://www.legislationline.org/download/id/4339/file/221_POLIT_MOL_11%20March%202013_en.pdf|accessdate=2020-04-22|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226022243/https://www.legislationline.org/download/id/4339/file/221_POLIT_MOL_11%20March%202013_en.pdf|archivedate=2020-02-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>2005年，[[捷克|捷克共和国]]有人请愿禁止宣传共产主义； 2007年，有人提议对法律进行修正，禁止共产主义标志。两次尝试均告失败。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Communists in Czech Politics|url=http://www.expats.cz/prague/article/politics/communists-in-czech-politics/|accessdate=2017-08-17|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817161846/http://www.expats.cz/prague/article/politics/communists-in-czech-politics/|archivedate=2017-08-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>Joint amicus curiae brief, p. 13</ref>

=== {{爱沙尼亚}} ===
